{
  "texts": [
    "As genome data grows exponentially, it becomes increasingly challenging for algorithms to scale and perform analyses on large datasets within a reasonable time frame.",
    "Also, genomes exhibit extensive structural and functional variability.",
    "Developing algorithms that can accommodate this variability and provide robust results is a challenge.",
    "Moreover, bridging the gap between raw genomic data and existing biological knowledge databases is a complex process, as it requires advanced natural language processing and semantic integration techniques.",
    "Traditionally, clinical practice has been based on the concept of 'one therapy fits all'."
  ]
}